 Laleye Dipo in Minna The federal and Niger State Governments are working towards securing the release of two Chinese nationals who were kidnapped by gunmen over two months ago at the new Zungeru Hydro Electric Dam project site in Niger State. During the raid by the gunmen, three Nigerians were shot dead, while another Chinese national was reportedly injured in the incident that took place on January 5 this year. The state Commissioner for Local Government and Internal Security, Mr. Emmanuel Umar, giving an update on the security situation in the state in Minna yesterday, said both the federal and the state government “are on top of the situation.” He did not give further details. Umar disclosed that following ‘security breaches’ in Munya Local Government Area last week, “the government has reviewed the entire security architecture in the area” to ensure the lives and property of the people there are guaranteed. ” Very soon, large movement of troops will be seen around the area,” Umar said, before confirming that two security agents were injured in the invasion of the area by bandits with one still hospitalised and the other discharged from the hospital. The commissioner said during the period under review, men of the troops of the 32 field artillery neutralised some bandits in Mariga LGA of the state and also recovered over 300 cattle and 73 sheep rustled by gunmen. Some of the recovered cattle have been kept in Kontagora awaiting identification by their owners while a few of them died as a result stress.